<Layout title="Section 11 – Nursing Skills Simulation">
  <h1>Section 11: Nursing Skills Simulation</h1>
  <p><em>Competency 7093.4.11 – Applies Nursing Process/Clinical Judgment Model</em></p>
  <p>
    Use simulation to potentiate skill performance in the lab and demonstrate selected
    nursing clinical skills digitally.
  </p>

  <h2 id="simulation-purpose">Purpose of Simulation in Nursing Education</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Provides a safe, risk-free environment to practice clinical skills before patient contact.</li>
    <li>Reinforces the nursing process and clinical judgment model in realistic scenarios.</li>
    <li>Promotes patient safety, communication efficiency, and critical thinking.</li>
    <li>Allows repetitive practice to build confidence and competence.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="sls">Simulation Learning System (SLS)</h2>
  <p>
    Elsevier's SLS guides preparation for in-person simulation labs. Access via Evolve
    using course ID: <strong>154359_dswanson86_1001</strong>
  </p>
  <p>Required SLS scenarios for D442:</p>

  <h3>SLS 2.0 Fundamental Scenario 5 – Lisa Rae</h3>
  <p><strong>Focus: Fall and Pressure Ulcer Risk Assessment</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Apply the Morse Fall Scale to assess Lisa Rae's fall risk.</li>
    <li>Identify pressure injury risk factors using the Braden Scale.</li>
    <li>Implement appropriate fall prevention and skin integrity interventions.</li>
    <li>Document findings and communicate risk level to the care team.</li>
    <li>Apply the Clinical Judgment Measurement Model (CJMM): Recognize cues → Analyze → Prioritize → Generate solutions → Take action → Evaluate.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="tip">
    <strong>💡 Study Focus for Lisa Rae</strong>
    Review Section 4 (Personal Hygiene/Skin Integrity) and Section 5 (Mobility/Fall Prevention)
    before completing this scenario.
  </div>

  <h3>SLS 2.0 Fundamental Scenario 2 – Bernadette Jackson</h3>
  <p><strong>Focus: Confusion in an Older Adult with Infection</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Recognize atypical presentation of infection in an older adult (altered mental status instead of classic fever/pain).</li>
    <li>Identify signs and symptoms of urinary tract infection and sepsis.</li>
    <li>Perform focused assessment: vital signs, mental status, urine characteristics, catheter care.</li>
    <li>Develop an SBAR report and implement nursing interventions.</li>
    <li>Evaluate effectiveness of interventions and revise plan as needed.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="tip">
    <strong>💡 Study Focus for Bernadette Jackson</strong>
    Review Section 9 (Elimination/CAUTI Prevention) and Section 2 (Nursing Process/CJMM)
    before completing this scenario.
  </div>

  <h2 id="shadow-health">Shadow Health Digital Clinical Experiences (DCE)</h2>
  <p>
    Shadow Health is a virtual reality simulation platform for practicing patient assessments.
    Scores are sent directly to WGU. Technical support: <strong>1-800-860-3241</strong>
  </p>
  <p>Required DCEs for D442 (Ticket to Ride — must score ≥ 80%):</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Gerontology: Pain – Edward Carter</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Gerontology: Mobility – Robert Hall</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="simumed">SimuMED Kit Practice</h2>
  <p>
    Use your SimuMED physical simulation kit to practice hands-on skills before lab.
    Key components for practice:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Injection Pad (adjustable arm/leg):</strong> Practice intradermal, subcutaneous, and intramuscular injections.</li>
    <li><strong>IV Training Pad:</strong> Practice IV access and maintenance techniques.</li>
    <li><strong>Central Line model:</strong> Practice sterile technique for central line care.</li>
    <li><strong>Deep Wound Stand:</strong> Practice wound care and sterile dressing changes.</li>
    <li><strong>Tracheostomy Tube / Stoma Simulator:</strong> Practice airway care and ostomy management.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="lab-prep">Lab Intensive Preparation Checklist</h2>
  <p>Complete the following before attending the D442 lab intensive:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Complete all <strong>Ticket to Ride</strong> requirements with ≥ 80% scores (Shadow Health DCEs and HESI Patient Reviews) at least two weeks before lab.</li>
    <li>Complete <strong>SLS Scenario 5 (Lisa Rae)</strong> and <strong>SLS Scenario 2 (Bernadette Jackson)</strong>.</li>
    <li>Review <strong>Clinical Skills</strong> for each lab skill and print checklists from the Checklist tab.</li>
    <li>Practice with your <strong>SimuMED kit</strong> for hands-on skill repetition.</li>
    <li>Review all 11 course sections and associated competencies.</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="note">
    <strong>📌 Reminder</strong>
    You must pass the On Ground Lab Performance Assessment to progress to D444 Adult Health I
    Clinical Intensive. Adequate preparation through simulation is essential.
  </div>

  <h2 id="key-terms">Key Terms</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SLS:</strong> Simulation Learning System — Elsevier's platform for virtual simulation scenarios.</li>
    <li><strong>DCE:</strong> Digital Clinical Experience — Shadow Health's virtual patient simulation.</li>
    <li><strong>SimuMED:</strong> Physical simulation kit for hands-on skill practice.</li>
    <li><strong>CJMM:</strong> Clinical Judgment Measurement Model — six cognitive skills used throughout simulation and clinical practice.</li>
    <li><strong>Ticket to Ride:</strong> D442 prerequisite requirements (Shadow Health DCEs + HESI reviews) that must be completed with ≥ 80% before attending lab.</li>
  </ul>
</Layout>
